# Data model (selected)

This summarizes key models observed in app/prisma/schema.prisma. MySQL 8 provider; decimals for money.

- User — core identity with role, settings, password (encrypted), email (encrypted + hash), JWT key; relations to accounts, notifications, plaid items, reconciliation periods
- Account — logical workspace; relations to budgets, categories, account registers, snapshots, savings goals, bills, reconciliation periods
- UserAccount — membership and permissions per account (allowed budgets/register-ids JSON)
- AccountInvite + AccountInviteAccount — invite flows and permissions at invite time
- Budget — scope for registers, notifications, bills, reconciliation periods
- AccountRegister — the ledger register (type, balances, credit/loan fields, statement interval, Plaid info, crypto wallet fields, asset/depreciation fields). Relations to entries, reoccurrences, categories (default payment/interest), snapshots, savings goals, crypto chains/balances, CashOnHand
- CashOnHand — per-register denominations and auditing timestamps
- RegisterEntry — ledger row with amount, balance, types, flags (projected/pending/balance/manual), Plaid linkage, category
- RegisterEntryType — classifier for entries
- Category — hierarchical categories with parent/children, shared by entries/reoccurrences/splits and account defaults
- Reoccurrence (+ ReoccurrenceSplit, ReoccurrenceSkip, ReoccurrencePlaidNameAlias) — recurring schedule, amount adjustment rules, splits to other registers, aliasing for Plaid matching
- Interval — reference table for schedule/amount adjustment intervals and statement intervals
- SavingsGoal — transfer between source and target registers with priority/sort rules and category
- Snapshot models — AccountSnapshot, AccountRegisterSnapshot, RegisterEntrySnapshot capture point-in-time copies
- ReconciliationPeriod + ReconciliationItem — statement reconciliation windows, closing adjustments, clear status
- Bills — BillProfile (ties to Reoccurrence) and BillInstance with due dates, statuses, amounts, reminders
- Notifications — NotificationEvent and NotificationDismissal per user/budget/kind
- Integrations/logging — PlaidItem, PlaidSyncCursor, PlaidSyncLog; IntegrationAlert; IntegrationJobLog; OpenAiRequestLog
- RSA keys — Rsa table (DB-held keys, default/archived flags)
- AccountType — register classification flags (credit/accrues_balance_growth), class (fiat/crypto/etc.)
- Crypto — EvmChain, CryptoRegisterChain (register to chain mapping), CryptoTokenBalance (network balances, price/value)

Notable constraints/indices (selection):
- Uniques/hashes for encrypted identifiers (emailHash, plaidAccessTokenHash, walletAddressHash, plaidIdHash)
- Category uniqueness uses a functional index defined in migrations (not expressible directly in Prisma)
- BillInstance uniqueness on (billProfileId, dueAt)
- Various covering indices for performance on foreign keys and activity windows
